  <section class="rbp-section rbp-section--soft" aria-label="How Remote Business Partner works">
    <div class="rbp-wrap">
      <div class="rbp-section-head">
        <div class="rbp-kicker">How it works</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-title">A clearer path from problem to support</h2>
        <p class="rbp-copy">Instead of another wall of cards, users get a simple decision flow that explains what happens next.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rbp-process">
        <div class="rbp-step"><h3>Pick your business need</h3><p>Start with the outcome you are trying to achieve, not a confusing internal category.</p></div>
        <div class="rbp-step"><h3>Review the best pathway</h3><p>Compare whether the right next step is a service, resource, membership route or partner offer.</p></div>
        <div class="rbp-step"><h3>Take action quickly</h3><p>Open the relevant page, make an enquiry, download a resource or browse available options.</p></div>
        <div class="rbp-step"><h3>Build from there</h3><p>Use the platform as a continuing business support hub as your needs change.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rbp-dark-section" aria-label="Core service pathways">
    <div class="rbp-wrap">
      <div class="rbp-section-head">
        <div class="rbp-kicker">Service pathways</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-title">Support options without the usual maze</h2>
        <p class="rbp-copy">The main pathways stay visible, but the page no longer relies on repeating the same card grid forever. Revolutionary, apparently.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rbp-pathways">
        <a class="rbp-pathway" href="/pages/core-services">
          <span class="rbp-pathway__mark">CORE</span>
          <span><h3>Core Services and Advisory</h3><p>Structured support across strategy, systems, operations and business improvement.</p><span>Explore core services →</span></span>
        </a>
        <a class="rbp-pathway" href="/collections/on-demand-services">
          <span class="rbp-pathway__mark">TASK</span>
          <span><h3>On-Demand Services</h3><p>Practical support for specific business tasks, admin work, projects and specialist needs.</p><span>Browse on-demand services →</span></span>
        </a>
        <a class="rbp-pathway" href="/pages/membership">
          <span class="rbp-pathway__mark">MEM</span>
          <span><h3>Membership</h3><p>A structured pathway for businesses that want ongoing access to selected benefits and support routes.</p><span>View membership →</span></span>
        </a>
        <a class="rbp-pathway" href="/pages/help-centre">
          <span class="rbp-pathway__mark">HUB</span>
          <span><h3>Business Hub and Help Centre</h3><p>Guides, support articles and resources to help users find answers before they need a conversation.</p><span>Visit the Help Centre →</span></span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rbp-section" aria-label="Built for Australian SMEs">
    <div class="rbp-wrap rbp-sme">
      <div class="rbp-section-head">
        <div class="rbp-kicker">Built for SMEs</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-title">Designed around how Australian SMEs actually work</h2>
        <p class="rbp-copy">SMEs need practical pathways, not a dense services catalogue wearing a nice gradient suit. This section makes the positioning more specific, credible and human.</p>
        <div class="rbp-actions" style="margin-top:28px">
          <a class="rbp-btn rbp-btn--primary" href="/pages/core-services">Find business support</a>
          <a class="rbp-btn" style="border:1px solid var(--rbp-line); color:var(--rbp-blue); background:var(--rbp-white)" href="/pages/contact">Talk to the team</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rbp-sme__features">
        <div class="rbp-mini"><strong>Flexible, not bloated</strong><span>Use support as needed instead of committing to heavy retainers before you know what fits.</span></div>
        <div class="rbp-mini"><strong>Advice plus action</strong><span>Move from guidance into resources, services or partner options without starting again.</span></div>
        <div class="rbp-mini"><strong>Curated pathways</strong><span>Make the next step clearer for users who are busy running the business, because apparently that matters.</span></div>
        <div class="rbp-mini"><strong>Built for decisions</strong><span>Help users compare their options and choose a route with less friction.</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rbp-section rbp-section--soft" aria-label="Membership and marketplace pathways">
    <div class="rbp-wrap">
      <div class="rbp-section-head">
        <div class="rbp-kicker">Choose your role</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-title">Use RBP as an SME or as a partner</h2>
        <p class="rbp-copy">This split creates two clean conversion paths instead of asking every visitor to decode whether they are buyer, member, provider or lost traveller.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rbp-split">
        <div class="rbp-split-card rbp-split-card--member">
          <span class="rbp-split-card__label">For SMEs</span>
          <h3>Become an RBP member</h3>
          <p>Access a structured membership pathway for business resources, selected benefits and support options.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use one organised business support hub</li>
            <li>Access resources and selected member routes</li>
            <li>Move faster from problem to action</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="rbp-btn rbp-btn--light" href="/pages/membership">Explore membership</a>
        </div>
        <div class="rbp-split-card rbp-split-card--partner">
          <span class="rbp-split-card__label">For providers</span>
          <h3>List your offer on the marketplace</h3>
          <p>Reach Australian SMEs through a clearer partner pathway for services, products and offers.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Present your offer to a focused SME audience</li>
            <li>Support marketplace and partner discovery</li>
            <li>Create a cleaner path for business enquiries</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="rbp-btn rbp-btn--light" href="/pages/marketplace">Apply as a partner</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rbp-section" aria-label="Business resources for Australian SMEs">
    <div class="rbp-wrap">
      <div class="rbp-section-head">
        <div class="rbp-kicker">Resources</div>
        <h2 class="rbp-title">Useful business resources, not decorative blog confetti</h2>
        <p class="rbp-copy">Resource cards now communicate practical value and content type, which helps the section feel like a real tool rather than filler.</p>
